The paper deals with algorithms for drawing trees and graphs, which are typical topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves analyzing the width and area of the drawings, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The connection between LR-drawings and outerplanar straight-line drawings suggests that the paper may also be relevant to graph theory (cs.GT) and possibly even social networks (cs.SI).
